20tin%2C%20then%20sprinkle%20the%20top%20with%20the%20extra%20kibbled%20wheat%20and%20sesame%20seeds.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%226%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3EBake%20in%20the%20fully%20preheated%20oven%20for%2050%20to%2060%20minutes.%20Remove%20the%20tin%2010%20to%2015%20minutes%20before%20the%20end%20of%20cooking%20time%20and%20return%20to%20the%20oven%20to%20continue%20baking.%20Tap%20the%20base%20of%20the%20bread%20to%20check%20it's%20cooked%20%E2%80%94%20it%20should%20sound%20hollow.%20Cool%20on%20a%20wire%20rack.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b403b0a-bd48-4fa7-8603-3d56af4e323f%5C%22%3EPesto%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20chef%20holding%20up%20a%20herb%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68398e556ffb6822ec61c689%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EO'Connell%20changes%20the%20ingredients%20he%20includes%20in%20pesto%20depending%20on%20what's%20in%20season.%3Cp%3EKim%20Schewitz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20make%20pesto%20in%20minutes%2C%20and%20it%20keeps%20for%20weeks%20covered%20with%20a%20layer%20of%20olive%20oil%20in%20a%20jar%20in%20the%20fridge%2C%20O'Connell%20said.%20It%20also%20freezes%20well%2C%20but%20for%20best%20results%2C%20don't%20add%20the%20Parmesan%20cheese%20until%20it%20has%20defrosted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20make%20pesto%2C%20you%20have%20a%20sauce%20for%20chicken%2C%20fish%2C%20lamb%2C%20beans.%20You%20can%20have%20it%20just%20on%20toast%20with%20a%20poached%20egg%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20pesto%20is%20made%20with%20basil%20and%20pine%20nuts%2C%20but%20you%20can%20substitute%20these%20for%20lots%20of%20different%20things.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20always%20going%20to%20be%20something%20in%20season%20at%20any%20time%20of%20the%20year%20that%20you%20can%20use%20in%20that%20recipe%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVariations