g%20yolks%2C%20preferably%20free%20range%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%2F4%20teaspoon%20salt%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20pinch%20of%20English%20mustard%20or%201%2F4%20teaspoon%20French%20mustard%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20dessertspoon%20white%20wine%20vinegar%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E225ml%20oil%20(sunflower%20or%20olive%20oil%20or%20a%20mixture)%20-%20we%20use%20175ml%20sunflower%20oil%20and%2050ml%20oil%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMethod%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3EPut%20the%20egg%20yolks%20into%20a%20bowl%20with%20the%20salt%2C%20mustard%2C%20and%20the%20white%20wine%20vinegar.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3EPut%20the%20oil%20into%20a%20measuring%20jug.%20Take%20a%20whisk%20in%20one%20hand%20and%20the%20oil%20in%20the%20other%20and%20drip%20the%20oil%20onto%20the%20egg%20yolks%2C%20drop%20by%20drop%2C%20whisking%20at%20the%20same%20time%20to%20create%20an%20emulsion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%223%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3EWithin%20a%20minute%2C%20you%20will%20notice%20that%20the%20mixture%20is%20beginning%20to%20thicken.%20When%20this%20happens%2C%20you%20can%20add%20the%20oil%20a%20little%20faster%2C%20but%20don't%20get%20too%20complacent%20or%20it%20will%20suddenly%20curdle%20(split)%20because%20the%20egg%20yolks%20can%20only%20absorb%20the%20oil%20at%20a%20certain%20pace.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETaste%20and%20add%20a%20little%20more%20seasoning%20and%20vinegar%20if%20necessary.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffoods-can-make-from-scratch-avoid-ultra-processed-food-chef-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748679782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68399708ca50259add4d558f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffoods-can-make-from-scratch-avoid-ultra-processed-food-chef-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ultra-processed%20foods%20are%20convenient.%20But%20some%20thin